Founded in 1989, Jovenes, Inc. is a non-profit organization in Los Angeles whose mission has been to assist homeless and displaced young adults in primarily, but not exclusively Pico-Union/Westlake, Echo Park, South Central, East Los Angeles, Long Beach and Hollywood. It was founded by Fr. Richard Estrada, CMF originally an outreach to underage immigrants in 1969.
"Jovenes" is Spanish for youth, and the agency focuses its efforts on helping disenfranchised youth Its new facility, the Lloyd Monserratt Pleasant House opened in May 2006.
